10 Cursed be you, ancient she‑wolf, 11 who more than all the other beasts have prey 12 for your hunger without end dark!
13 O heaven, in whose turning it seems one may think 14 the conditions down here to be transmuted, 15 when will it come for which this departs?
16 We went with slow and scarce steps, 17 and I attentive to the shadows, that I heard 18 pitiably weeping and lamenting;
19 and by chance I heard “Sweet Mary!” 20 in front of us to call thus in the weeping 21 as a woman does who is in childbirth;
22 and to follow: “Poor you were so much, 23 as much as can be seen for that hospice 24 where you bore your holy bearing.”

